HEADWORD: Yearnings
<hw>Yearn"ings</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>geirnan</ets>, <ets>geyrnan</ets>, to rum. See 4th
<er>Earn</er>.]</ety> <def>The maws, or stomachs, of young calves, used
as a rennet for curdling milk.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>year-old</ent>⟦br⟧
